  <entry>
    <title>Build a Deep Learning Environment on Ubuntu</title>
    <link href="https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/10/18/build-dl-env-on-ubuntu/"/>
    <id>https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/10/18/build-dl-env-on-ubuntu/</id>
    <published>2018-10-18T06:17:34.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-10-18T07:23:43.933Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="/2018/10/18/build-dl-env-on-ubuntu/maxresdefault.jpg" alt="1"><br><a id="more"></a></p><h1 id="Set-grub-resolution"><a href="#Set-grub-resolution" class="headerlink" title="Set grub resolution"></a>Set grub resolution</h1><p>Edit <code>/etc/default/grub</code> and find<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="comment"># The resolution used on graphical terminal </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># note that you can use only modes which your graphic card supports via VBE </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># you can see them in real GRUB with the command 'vbeinfo' </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># GRUB_GFXMODE=640Ã—480</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>Set <code>GRUB_GFXMODE</code> as your screen resolution and uncomment it. For example:<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">GRUB_GFXMODE=1920x1080</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>At last <code>sudo update-grub</code> and restart ubuntu.</p><h1 id="Install-Nvidia-GPU-driver"><a href="#Install-Nvidia-GPU-driver" class="headerlink" title="Install Nvidia GPU driver"></a>Install Nvidia GPU driver</h1><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">sudo add-apt-repository ppa:graphics-drivers/ppa</span><br><span class="line">sudo apt-get update</span><br><span class="line">sudo apt-get install nvidia-370</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Test your driver by input <code>nvidia-smi</code> in your terminal.</p><h1 id="Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN"><a href="#Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN" class="headerlink" title="Install CUDA and cuDNN"></a>Install CUDA and cuDNN</h1><p>Download <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CUDA</a> and <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cuDNN</a>.<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Install CUDA</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> /path/to/cuda/run/file</span><br><span class="line">sudo sh cuda_***.run</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Install cuDNN</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> /path/to/cudnn/tar</span><br><span class="line">tar -zxvf cudnn_***.tar.gz</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> cuda/include/</span><br><span class="line">sudo cp cudnn.h /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda/include/</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> ../lib64</span><br><span class="line">sudo cp lib* /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda/lib64/</span><br><span class="line">sudo chmod a+r /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda/include/cudnn.h /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda/lib64/libcudnn*</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h1 id="3-Install-Tensorflow-in-Anaconda"><a href="#3-Install-Tensorflow-in-Anaconda" class="headerlink" title="3 Install Tensorflow in Anaconda"></a>3 Install Tensorflow in Anaconda</h1><p>Download <a href="https://www.anaconda.com/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anaconda</a>.<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> /path/to/anaconda/install/file</span><br><span class="line">sh Anaconda3-***.sh</span><br><span class="line">conda create --name set_your_env_name_here python=3.5</span><br><span class="line">activate set_your_env_name_here</span><br><span class="line">pip install tensorflow-gpu</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h1 id="4-Switch-Multi-Version-of-CUDA"><a href="#4-Switch-Multi-Version-of-CUDA" class="headerlink" title="4 Switch Multi Version of CUDA"></a>4 Switch Multi Version of CUDA</h1><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">sudo rm -rf /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda</span><br><span class="line">sudo ln -s /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda-9.0 /usr/<span class="built_in">local</span>/cuda</span><br><span class="line">nvcc --version</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/2018/10/18/build-dl-env-on-ubuntu/maxresdefault.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
