  <entry>
    <title>Set Server Auto Restart Regularly</title>
    <link href="https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/10/18/server-audo-restart/"/>
    <id>https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/10/18/server-audo-restart/</id>
    <published>2018-10-18T05:46:57.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-10-18T07:18:12.234Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Set-System-Time-Zone"><a href="#Set-System-Time-Zone" class="headerlink" title="Set System Time Zone"></a>Set System Time Zone</h1><p>Check your system time and time zone by <code>date -R</code><br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Shanghai /etc/localtime</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Replace /Asia/Shanghai with  the time zone you want to set</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><a id="more"></a><h1 id="Install-Crontab-and-Set-Auto-Restart"><a href="#Install-Crontab-and-Set-Auto-Restart" class="headerlink" title="Install Crontab and Set Auto Restart"></a>Install Crontab and Set Auto Restart</h1><h2 id="Install-Crontab"><a href="#Install-Crontab" class="headerlink" title="Install Crontab"></a>Install Crontab</h2><p>1 Centos<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">yum install vixie-cron crontabs</span><br><span class="line">chkconfig crond on</span><br><span class="line">service crond start</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>2 Debian<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">apt-get install cron</span><br><span class="line">/etc/init.d/cron restart</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h2 id="Set-Auto-Restart"><a href="#Set-Auto-Restart" class="headerlink" title="Set Auto Restart"></a>Set Auto Restart</h2><p>Modify script by <code>crontab -e</code> and add<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">0 6 * * * /sbin/reboot</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>which means restart at 6:00 am everyday.</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">/etc/rc.d/init.d/crond stop</span><br><span class="line">/etc/rc.d/init.d/crond start</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;h1 id=&quot;Set-System-Time-Zone&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Set-System-Time-Zone&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Set System Time Zone&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Set System Time Zone&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Check your system time and time zone by &lt;code&gt;date -R&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight bash&quot;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;gutter&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;code&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line&quot;&gt;cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Shanghai /etc/localtime&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;comment&quot;&gt;# Replace /Asia/Shanghai with  the time zone you want to set&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
