    <title>Install Tensorflow on Windows 10</title>
    <link href="https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/02/26/install%20tensorflow%20on%20win10/"/>
    <id>https://fdujyy.github.io/2018/02/26/install tensorflow on win10/</id>
    <published>2018-02-26T14:42:54.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-02-27T08:10:17.959Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="1-Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN"><a href="#1-Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN" class="headerlink" title="1 Install CUDA and cuDNN"></a>1 <strong>Install CUDA and cuDNN</strong></h3><p>Download <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CUDA Toolkit</a> and <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cuDNN</a>. Choose the version your GPU support.</p><h3 id="2-Install-Anaconda"><a href="#2-Install-Anaconda" class="headerlink" title="2 Install Anaconda"></a>2 <strong>Install Anaconda</strong></h3><h4 id="2-1-Download-and-install-Anaconda"><a href="#2-1-Download-and-install-Anaconda" class="headerlink" title="2.1 Download and install Anaconda"></a>2.1 <strong>Download and install Anaconda</strong></h4><p>Download <a href="https://www.anaconda.com/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anaconda</a> and tick “<strong>Add Anaconda to my PATh environment variable</strong>“ during installing.</p><h4 id="2-2-Switch-the-software-source-of-pip-and-conda"><a href="#2-2-Switch-the-software-source-of-pip-and-conda" class="headerlink" title="2.2 Switch the software source of pip and conda"></a>2.2 <strong>Switch the software source of pip and conda</strong></h4><p>Domestic mirrors can accelerate the download speed of installing packages using pip and conda.<br>There are some mirrors in China for both pip and conda.<br><a id="more"></a></p><h4 id="2-2-1-Pip"><a href="#2-2-1-Pip" class="headerlink" title="2.2.1 Pip"></a>2.2.1 <strong>Pip</strong></h4><p><strong>Pip source</strong>:</p><pre><code>1. 阿里云 http://mirrors.aliyun.com/pypi/simple/ 2. 中国科技大学 https://pypi.mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/simple/ 3. 豆瓣(douban) http://pypi.douban.com/simple/ 4. 清华大学 https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple/ 5. 中国科学技术大学 http://pypi.mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/simple/</code></pre><p><strong>Temporary change source</strong>: add <code>-i</code> after the command line.<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">pip install package_name -i https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple/</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>pip install package_name -i <a href="https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple/</a></p><p><strong>Permenent change source</strong></p><h5 id="Linux"><a href="#Linux" class="headerlink" title="Linux"></a><strong>Linux</strong></h5><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">sudo vi ~/.pip/pip.conf</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Change the file to</span></span><br><span class="line">[global]</span><br><span class="line">index-url = https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h5 id="Windows"><a href="#Windows" class="headerlink" title="Windows"></a><strong>Windows</strong></h5><p>Create a <code>ini</code> file <code>pip.ini</code> in <code>C:\Users\your_username\pip</code> and change the content to:<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">[global]</span><br><span class="line">index-url = https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h4 id="2-2-2-Conda"><a href="#2-2-2-Conda" class="headerlink" title="2.2.2 Conda"></a>2.2.2 <strong>Conda</strong></h4><p><strong>Conda source</strong>:</p><pre><code>1. 清华大学 https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/anaconda/pkgs/free/</code></pre><p>Type in the command line:<br><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">conda config --add channels https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/anaconda/pkgs/free/</span><br><span class="line">conda config --<span class="built_in">set</span> show_channel_urls yes</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>Or in Linux and Mac OS, edit <code>~/.condarc</code>:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">channels: </span><br><span class="line">- https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/anaconda/pkgs/free/ </span><br><span class="line">- defaults</span><br><span class="line">show_channel_urls: yes</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="3-Install-Tensorflow-in-Anaconda"><a href="#3-Install-Tensorflow-in-Anaconda" class="headerlink" title="3 Install Tensorflow in Anaconda"></a>3 <strong>Install Tensorflow in Anaconda</strong></h3><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">conda create --name set_your_env_name_here python=3.5</span><br><span class="line">activate set_your_env_name_here</span><br><span class="line">pip install tensorflow-gpu</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;h3 id=&quot;1-Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#1-Install-CUDA-and-cuDNN&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;1 Install CUDA and cuDNN&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;1 &lt;strong&gt;Install CUDA and cuDNN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download &lt;a href=&quot;https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;CUDA Toolkit&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;cuDNN&lt;/a&gt;. Choose the version your GPU support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;2-Install-Anaconda&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#2-Install-Anaconda&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;2 Install Anaconda&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2 &lt;strong&gt;Install Anaconda&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&quot;2-1-Download-and-install-Anaconda&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#2-1-Download-and-install-Anaconda&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;2.1 Download and install Anaconda&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2.1 &lt;strong&gt;Download and install Anaconda&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.anaconda.com/download/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Anaconda&lt;/a&gt; and tick “&lt;strong&gt;Add Anaconda to my PATh environment variable&lt;/strong&gt;“ during installing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;2-2-Switch-the-software-source-of-pip-and-conda&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#2-2-Switch-the-software-source-of-pip-and-conda&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;2.2 Switch the software source of pip and conda&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2.2 &lt;strong&gt;Switch the software source of pip and conda&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Domestic mirrors can accelerate the download speed of installing packages using pip and conda.&lt;br&gt;There are some mirrors in China for both pip and conda.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
